+  // "Unable to submit request because it must include at least one parts field".
+  // The @ai-sdk/google converter drops assistant text/reasoning parts whose text
+  // is empty (`part.text.length === 0 ? undefined : ...` then filters), so a
+  // message that holds only empty-text parts serializes to `parts: []` and the
+  // whole request 400s. The usual source is the empty "structural separator" text
+  // part that Anthropic adaptive-thinking turns persist between step-start
+  // boundaries (see message-v2.ts): replayed to a Gemini compaction model as a
+  // cross-model turn it has no signed reasoning to trigger " " padding, survives
+  // as text: "", and convertToModelMessages splits it into a lone empty step.
+  // Mirror the converter (drop empty text/reasoning) and drop newly-empty
+  // messages, exactly like the @ai-sdk/anthropic and @ai-sdk/amazon-bedrock
+  // blocks above. This is lossless for Gemini since the converter discards those
+  // parts regardless (empty reasoning is dropped even when it carries a
